    <briefdescription>
<para><htmlonly> &lt;span class=&quot;mlabel&quot;&gt;Driver Operations&lt;/span&gt; </htmlonly> SPI driver operations </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>This is the driver API structure any SPI driver needs to define. It contains function pointers to the operations the driver implements, as well as any other driver-specific constant data.</para>
<para>Members marked with <htmlonly> &lt;span class=&quot;op-badge op-req&quot; title=&quot;This operation MUST be implemented by the driver.&quot;&gt;REQ&lt;/span&gt;</htmlonly> MUST be set by the driver, whereas those marked with <htmlonly> &lt;span class=&quot;op-badge op-opt&quot; title=&quot;This operation MAY optionally be implemented by the driver.&quot;&gt;OPT&lt;/span&gt;</htmlonly> are optional. <simplesect kind="see"><para><ref refid="group__device__model_1gada5ba4aca9e0662ccebb2232c7256419" kindref="member">DEVICE_DT_INST_DEFINE()</ref> </para>
</simplesect>
<simplesect kind="see"><para><ref refid="group__device__model_1gac49e26fbe91a14307d5ea08d41561dd1" kindref="member">DEVICE_DT_DEFINE()</ref> </para>
</simplesect>
<simplesect kind="see"><para><ref refid="device_8h_1aa0cdc799fc0b9c80eb29f989eec86707" kindref="member">DEVICE_API()</ref> </para>
</simplesect>
</para>
    </detaileddescription>
